The interossei, hypothenars and thenars are responsible for much of the appreciable bulk of the hand. 
The interossei and hypothenars are innervated by the ulnar nerve, while the thenars are innervated by the median nerve. An ulnar neuropathy can cause a selective loss of bulk of the hypothenars and interossei, as seen here:

The dorsal and palmar interossei get their names from their origins: they arise from between the metacarpals     in the palm of the hand. A useful     mnemonic for remembering the actions of the interossei is DAB and PAD. The Dorsal interossei ABduct (DAB) the digits and the Palmar interossei ADduct (PAD) the digits     .
